def: To shake with short, abrupt risings and fallings, as a carriagemoving on rough ground; as, the coach jolts.
One who imposes.The imposers of these oaths might repent. Walton.
A genus of small spiral fresh-water gastropods having anoperculum.
In a dull manner; stupidly; slowly; sluggishly; without life orspirit.Supinely calm and dully innocent. G. Lyttelton.

A white to gray volcanic tufa, formed of decomposed trachyticcinders; -- sometimes used as a cement. Hence, a coarse sort ofplaster or mortar, durable in water, and used to line cisterns andother reservoirs of water. [Formerly written also tarras, tarrace,terras.]
A flying out or up. [Obs.] Bp. Hall.

A suffix indicating an act, a process, the result of an act ora process, a state; also, a characteristic (as a theory, doctrine,idiom, etc.); as, baptism, galvanism, organism, hypnotism, socialism,sensualism, Anglicism.
A small gold coin formerly current in England; a half angel.Eng. Cyc.
The art or practice of using or making telescopes.
The quality or condition of being spumy; spumescence.
